diff:1620299615:1620173155:=62,70d61%0a%3c #foxbegin 210506-111335-943340#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Difficulty using automated phone answering services %0a%3c -> - xiranw%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c In recent years, many businesses, instead of always having a human receptionist on the line, have switched to using automated phone answering systems to perform simple requests and/or route callers. While these systems reduce cost, they present usability challenges for callers with accents. My father, who has a Chinese accent, has complained to me a few times about how these systems are not able to interpret his responses correctly. The most memorable one was how the system asked him to say his phone number but could not interpret his pronunciation of eight. It also gave him no option to simply type his phone number, so it was a quite frustrating experience.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210506-111335-943340#%0a
