diff:1620173155:1619901273:=51,61c51%0a%3c #foxbegin 210505-000555-838160#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Technology forcing adaptation of accents %0a%3c -> - AlexanderW%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/speech-recognition-tech-is-yet-another-example-of-bias/%0a%3c %0a%3c A pertinent consequence of this accent discrimination is that technology is forcing people to change the way they speaking. Mainly, they are forced to Anglicize their name or other words, as well as even change or modulate their own accent to be more "American". But this seems to be against the ideals of technology, where technology conforms to the individual instead of the individual conforming to technology. This causes many people conflict between maintaining identity and being more 'understood', which further emphasizes the importance of diversifying the AI's training data, as David mentioned above.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 210505-000555-838160#%0a---%0a> %0a
